american express led regional marketing team charged with increasing revenues from 65 national and field accounts b in annual volume in va dc nc sc ga la and fl • created new source of retail revenue grew incremental revenue up to  over any previous retail programs created first hispanic retail marketing campaign encompassing new product positioning value statements bilingual direct mail and inlanguage radio negotiated participation from key merchant partners • shifted market share launched a geographictargeted direct mail and media program returned  and leveraged for the first time a concept of double “membership rewards tm” with a pool of merchants    product marketing director daleen technologies created product line encompassing billing bss ordering oss and care implemented and planned market strategy and execution for 5m software line 996   director of marketing bellsouth telecommunications selected by senior management team to act as internal consultant in the definition  launch of products and product features for several new lines of business in  latin american markets peru argentina guatemala and chile also held positions in consumer and long distance product management education education 992  99 mba university of north carolina at chapel hill  kenanflagler business school mastercard names craig vosburg president north america markets succeeding chris mcwilton  business wire mastercard names craig vosburg president north america markets succeeding chris mcwilton november  25  am eastern standard time purchase nybusiness wiremastercard today announced the appointment of craig vosburg to president north america markets effective january  26 this appointment comes as chris mcwilton announced he will leave mastercard on december  mcwilton joined mastercard in 2 as corporate controller and was appointed chief financial officer in october of the same year as cfo mcwilton played a critical role in the company’s successful initial public offering ipo in may  the mastercard ipo was the largest domestic ipo of  and the 2th largest domestic ipo in us history at the time he was named president of mastercard global accounts in  managing relationships for the companys largest customers he was then appointed president of us markets in  before assuming north american responsibilities in 2 prior to joining mastercard mcwilton had a year career with kpmg where he specialized in financial and sec reporting and was an sec reviewing partner “i want to acknowledge chris’s contributions to the growth and evolution of mastercard” said ajay banga president and chief executive officer mastercard “i’d also like to personally thank him for his commitment over the years in helping to make our company what it is today the entire company joins me in wishing chris and his family all the best going forward” as president north america markets vosburg will oversee the companys customerfacing activities in the united states and canada including sales business development strategy and relationship management with issuers merchants governments and acquirers he will join the company’s executive committee vosburg  was most recently the company’s chief product officer a role he held since april  2 in this role he led the development commercialization and management of the company’s global core products offerings which include consumer credit and debit commercial prepaid and loyalty solutions “i’m pleased to announce craig’s appointment his experience both global and domestic make him the ideal person to drive our business forward” said banga “i’m confident craig will have great success in his new role” vosburg brings global experience to the role gained through a decade of working in the asia pacific region with mastercard and earlier in his career with bain  company and at kearney vosburg joined mastercard in  as head of mastercard advisors in southeast asia greater china and south asiamiddle eastafrica in  he was named managing director of the mastercard advisors business in the us and canada in 2 vosburg was named group executive us market development responsible for managing and building relationships within the merchant and acquiring community he began his career working in commercial banking at corestates financial corporation vosburg is a past david rockefeller fellow at the partnership for new york city and currently sits on the board of directors of the new york botanical garden he holds a master of business administration from the wharton school at the university of pennsylvania and a bachelor of science in business administration from bucknell university changes to global product and middle east and africa leadership effective january  michael miebach will assume the role of chief product officer for the company replacing vosburg and will be based in new york he currently serves as president middle east and africa responsible for driving the evolution of payments and delivering increased value to mastercard stakeholders in markets across the region before joining mastercard in 2 miebach held several global positions including with barclays where he was the managing director for middle east and north africa and managing director for barclays africa he also held seniorlevel positions at citibank responsible for germany austria uk and turkey raghu malhotra will become president middle east and africa as of january  previously overseeing middle east and north africa malhotra will now add supervision of subsaharan africa and south africa markets to his responsibilities since  he has led several teams across south asia india and the middle east and africa prior to joining mastercard malhotra served in a variety of leadership roles across the consumer franchise and financial services businesses for citigroup american express and anz grindlays bank about mastercard mastercard nysema wwwmastercardcom is a technology company in the global payments industry we operate the world’s fastest payments processing network connecting consumers financial institutions merchants governments and businesses in more than 2 countries and territories mastercard’s products and solutions make everyday commerce activities – such as shopping traveling running a business and managing finances – easier more secure and more efficient for everyone follow us on twitter mastercardnews join the discussion on the beyond the transaction blog and subscribe for the latest news on the engagement bureau contacts mastercardseth eisen 9295setheisenmastercardcom release summary mastercard today announced the appointment of craig vosburg to president north america markets effective january  26 contacts mastercardseth eisen 9295setheisenmastercardcom search advanced news search advanced news search log in sign up mastercard names craig vosburg president north america markets succeeding chris mcwilton  global hub subscribe to our email alerts subscribe to our email alerts email address subscribe to press releases subscribe to blog postssubscribe to news briefs accept privacy i have read and understand mastercards privacy policy subscribe close engagement bureau home briefs press releases digital press kits images  infographics video gallery beyond the transaction blog innovation safety  security financial inclusion cashless pioneers trending topics sponsored blog authors our people contact us media contacts advertising sponsorships mastercard advisors cardholder questions globalenglishlatin americaspanishportugueseenglishasia pacificchinese simplifiedenglishjapanesecanadaenglisheuropefrenchgermanitalianspanishenglishdutchpolishturkishswedishhungarianukrainianczechrussiarussianmiddle eastafricaenglishfrencharabic mastercard united states home page newsroom blog our people investor relations careers select a locationenglishspanishportugueseenglishchinese simplifiedenglishjapaneseenglishfrenchgermanitalianspanishenglishdutchpolishturkishswedishhungarianukrainianczechrussianenglishfrencharabic all briefs press releases p